I'm Not sure if the second heading is RIDGE, or whether a "B" has been cut off and it should be BRIDGE. Note 2 - I presume some of the para. nos. have also been chopped off in the copying process, but context indicates what they must be. I have put the missing paragraph numbers back in or it won't make sense. It all reads as follows:, , "1) Blade body short and [...] sided. Almost square. St. face to septum.,4)Bevelled top with straight face to blade.,5) Socket shape rectang, with inturned flanges giving it a waisted appearance.,6) flat floor to socket with [...]-sided inturned flanges,7) Flanges: a) leaf-shaped, extending for c. 1cm below stop.
